demerit points
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:penalties incurred by motorists for traffic offences, expressed in numbers which when aggregated to a certain amount (currently 100 points) result in suspension of licence or disqualification from driving.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Jim Cameron writes: see Land Transport Act 1998, s.88. The British equivalent seems to be <i>penalty points</i> which are <i>totted up</i>.
